  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [ ] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (bab38d6 2022-05-06T00:07:49.001076+00:00)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge test\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\ncontract MyContractTest is Test {\r\n  constructor() {\r\n    revert(\"failed to deploy\");\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  function testMyContract() public {\r\n    assertTrue(true);\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nRun `forge test` and you get:\r\n\r\n```\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  couldn't deploy: \r\n   0: deployment failed: Revert\r\n\r\nLocation:\r\n   /Users/runner/work/foundry/foundry/evm/src/executor/mod.rs:465\r\n\r\nBacktrace omitted. Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\nLocation: /Users/runner/work/foundry/foundry/forge/src/runner.rs:232\r\n\r\nBacktrace omitted. Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\n```\r\n\r\nIdeally forge would show a full trace, as you would see if `constructor()` was replaced with `setUp()`, but even just bubbling up the revert reason is sufficient since the current guidance is to use `setUp()` instead of constructors for test contracts.\r\n\r\nAlso just noting this was briefly discussed in https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/1291",
